Kisumu Governor Jack Ranguma has told off his opponents for fighting him instead of focusing on completing projects before the election.He said the time to start campaigns has not be been announced and leaders should unite to foster economic growth. &ldquo;We need the energy of all my opponents collectively in different positions. It is clear the electorate has its wishes, which we cannot go against,&rdquo; Ranguma said on Monday.Kisumu Senator Anyang&rsquo; Nyong&rsquo;o, Deputy Governor Ruth Odinga and businessman Hezron McObewa want to unseat Ranguma.Architect Christopher Ondiek, banker David Wayiera, WFP employee Asaka Nyangara and former lecturer Gordon Okumu have also declared their interest. The governor told the hopefuls they risk going into political oblivion if they fail to heed to the call of the people.